I bought the latest from STEREOLAB - Instant 0 in the Universe today. Good thing I did. This is a fine example of why I love the Lab. Ahh, I can't wait till there full length album comes out next year! Everyone must go buy it now! Go, go on...yes now!!! I can't explain how incredible and genius this ep is. Reminds me of Dots and Loops but a bit more disco in some sort. Good beats good beats! It's a bittersweet album...the influence that Mary had, and her voice is missing, but nontheless STEREOLAB continues on putting out material like no other. Besides Bjork, Leaticia Sadier is an incredible influence. I will stop now! I also bought Ladytron's SOFT CORE JUKEBOX...another album everyone should have. And I bought Affinity by Sarah Waters. I love me those lesbain themed novels :) Speaking of lesbian...The Lesbian Gay Film Festival will begin this Thursday and I really really want to go see Tipping the Velvet on Thursday night. There's a chance I might be going solo, but fuck it oh well, I have to see it or else...maybe Lani will say " fuck the fact that I'm pooped and that I haven't had a day off from work since Thursday, I'm just going to go with Hanna and watch Tipping the Velvet"...haha! Fuckin hell I have tons of homework to do, and I think I will ignore the fact and watch a movie instead. No, I'm just going to lay on my bed and listen to Stereolab all night. *** goodnight ***

*** It's the crack of dawn, I'm tired, but I can't sleep. So this might make no sence at all. Everything is cluttered inside. Here it goes....***

You try not to look into her eyes.
You fear she might find out you've been holding back
You fear she might see the emptyness.
She tries not to look into your eyes 
She fears you might find she's been holding back.
She fears you might find that emptyness 
You both look into each others eyes.
You realize, she realizes
You can't fool each other to long.

It's not what it seems
Nothing is right
Everything is wrong

You know, she knows
You explode
She implodes
You cry, she cries
You reach for her
She reaches for you
Words are limitations
Who needs words ?
All you both have to do is look much deeper into each others eyes, to find what each is yearning for.

Don't be surprised if you don't find any answers.
Don't be surprised if you do.
All it takes is time !

** It kinda makes sence **

Adrienne Rich  

Diving into the Wreck

First having read the book of myths,
and loaded the camera,
and checked the edge of the knife-blade,
I put on
the body-armor of black rubber
the absurd flippers
the grave and awkward mask.
I am having to do this
not like Cousteau with his
assiduous team
aboard the sun-flooded schooner
but here alone.

There is a ladder.
The ladder is always there
hanging innocently
close to the side of the schooner.
We know what it is for,
we who have used it.
Otherwise
it's a piece of maritime floss
some sundry equipment.

I go down.
Rung after rung and still
the oxygen immerses me.
the blue light 
the clear atoms
of our human air.
I go down.
My flippers cripple me,
I crawl like an insect down the ladder
and there is no one
to tell me when the ocean
will begin.

First the air is blue and then
it is bluer and then green and then
black and I am blacking out and yet
my mask is powerful
it pumps my blood with power
the sea is another story
the sea is not a question of power
I have to learn alone
to turn my body without force
in the deep element.

And now: it is easy to forget
what I came for 
among so many who have always
lived here
swaying their crennelated fans
between the reefs
and besides
you breathe differently down here.

I came to explore the wreck.
The words are purposes.
The words are maps.
I came to see the damage that was done
and the treasures that prevail.
I stroke the beam of my lamp
slowly along the flank
of something more permanent
than fish or weed

the thing I came for:
the wreck and not the story of the wreck
the thing itself and not the myth
the drowned face always staring
toward the sun
the evidence of damage
worn by salt and sway into this threadbare beauty
the ribs of the disaster
curving their assertion
among the tentative haunters.

This is the place.
And I am here, the mermaid whose dark hair
streams black, the merman in his armored body
We circle silently
about the wreck
we dive into the hold.
I am she: I am he

whose drowned face sleeps with open eyes
whose breasts still bear the stress
whose silver, copper, vermeil cargo lies
obscurely inside barrels
half-wedged and left to rot
we are the half-destroyed instruments
that once held to a course
the water-eaten log
the fouled compass

We are, I am, you are
by cowardice or courage
the one who find our way
back to this scene
carrying a knife, a camera
a book of myths
in which
our names do not appear.

Desi called me today, but I wasn't home! I called her back and to my surprise...she is in VEGAS!!! Fucken great...I wish I was in VEGAS!! She was already drunk and she told me not to make out with anyone...haha right! She said to wait until she came down here! FO SHO! With my luck I wouldn't doubt that happening! I'm very happy that she is in Vegas...having a blast!

I don't know what to do tonight!!! I'm confused!! I want to hang out with Natasha, get drunk, and make-out! On the other hand, I also want to hang out with the KIDS, get drunk and make-out! What to do..what to do??? I just want to have a fucken great time! I will!!! FO SHO!!

Um...apparantly Natasha got the FRIDA soundtrack that she's been wanting from someone else..FUCK!!! I got her the soundtrack first...now what? I'm going to keep the soundtrack for myself...and give her something else...but what??

I bought a shnazy black blouse today...wonderous!!

Tonight was very exciting! I left to Natasha's house around 10p.m...and we left to Aiko's house! Alle was there when we got there, which made me very happy to see him again! We all each did a line of coke! I feel awful for doing so, but at that moment I said fuck it! Now I am very awake, and I am hating every minute of it! Anyway. we took off, and went to the OHM! It was packed, and the music was fabulous! We danced till 3 in the morning! It was a different experience! I saw alot of girl on girl action, some weirdo guy started to break dance, and some other idiot decided to keep elbowing me through out the night! If it wasn't for Aiko, hitting him back, I don't think he would've stopped! He was on something badly! Besides that, I had great fun with the kids! Natasha was kinda weird throughout the night though! She still can't get over the night before! Apparantly she made out with one of her freinds...which happens to be  a girl...umhmmm in front of all these christians!!! And she was very "LIVELY"! I guess she is just embarrased about how she behaved! I didn't think it was such a big deal or that she acted wrong! But natasha will be natasha! That girl cracks me up! She says she will never drink again...I highly doubt it! Good times though!
And I will probably not sleep until who knows when..or eat! I am never doing coke again! It's just not my style anymore! It was fine while it lasted! Fuck, to think I have to go to work in about 6 hours or so...sacrilage!
